<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\00_stronghold\00_recruits\00_cv_library_skilltrainer_sagenerea</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>20</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do come back later, when I'll have more to teach you." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Still interested in my illusions, Fatebinder?" [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Nerea offers a deep bow.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'd like to train."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do you require training, Fatebinder?" She gives you stiff nod.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm available if you need some practice, Fatebinder."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes... yes, this will do nicely..."

A [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] peruses the library stacks, rubbing her palms together with expectation. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Clear your throat.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What are you doing here?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her eyes shoot open with panic and she utters a quick incantation. 

Your vision blurs, and suddenly there appear to be several copies of the [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] standing about, looking at you with anxious expressions. Some stand ready to fire off an additional spell, while others fiddle awkwardly with their garments.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What are you doing here?!" They all yell at once.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I own this place. What's your excuse?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fatebinder [Player Name], at your service."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Oh! I'm afraid I only know you by description, and they didn't exactly get it right. A moment's patience." 

The assembled Sages regard one of the identical speakers with expressions of doubt and worry.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You... you do?" With all of the Sages talking at once, it's difficult to make out the words. One of them stands out as more emphatic than the others. "Then the misunderstanding is mine. Just a moment."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] waves her hand and dispels the copies, which spread apart like mist until a breeze carries them away.

"That's better. You'll have to forgive me, it's an old defense mechanism against the lechers who ran the [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url]." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>She bows. "[url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Nerea, at your service. I shouldn't have been taken by surprise... I'm the newcomer here, after all. I was just so entranced by..." she gestures to the stacks of books and scrolls, "all of this." 

"I came to teach you, Fatebinder. That is, if you'll have me. With the destruction of the Citadel, I have to peddle my talents somewhere, and better up here than in the front lines."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Show me more illusions and it's a deal." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave] "I'm too busy at present. Perhaps later. Farewell."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Jump out and frighten her.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>